Few-shot learning refers to a chat AI's ability to understand and perform a new task based on just a handful of examples you provide in your prompt, without any additional training.
For instance, if you show the AI two or three examples of how you want data formatted—perhaps converting addresses into a specific structure.
It can often correctly format additional addresses following the same pattern, even though it was never explicitly trained on your particular formatting convention.
This capability emerges from the model's pre-training on diverse text, which taught it to recognize patterns and adapt to new contexts, making these systems remarkably flexible and able to handle tasks their creators never specifically anticipated, as long as you provide enough context in your conversation.
